The key problem: `codex plugin list --json` does **not** corroborate the changelog item in the way the proposal claims. It can confirm only that the local Codex binary supports that exact command. It cannot validate whether the scraper correctly extracted an upstream release item, whether the release item is complete, or whether other named commands exist. Extending it to opportunistic `codex <thing> --help` turns a narrow JSON feature into a fragile command-probing framework.

