# infprime

Infinitude-of-primes knowledge-ingestion pilot. Second clean instance of the
agQSL/qsens pipeline pattern (collect, analyse, context), built standalone so
the reusable template can be extracted from the qsens vs infprime diff.

Design: `infprime-pilot-design.md`. Plan: `infprime-pilot-plan.md`.

## Interactive class

This repo can also run as a self-paced class inside Codex or Claude Code.

```bash
git clone <repo-url>
cd infPrime
./course/preflight
./course/enter-codex
```

The launcher opens with a terminal title card, an ASCII pipeline diagram, and an
arrow-key path picker before entering Codex.

Or open Codex yourself:

```bash
codex "Start the infPrime class."
```

The class guide lives in `course/`. Codex reads `AGENTS.md`; Claude Code reads
`CLAUDE.md`.

## Layers

- **Collect.** `scan` appends candidate proofs to `data/candidates.jsonl`;
  `triage` (librarian plus number theorist) admits and labels them into
  `data/store.json`.
- **Analyse.** `analyse` runs the chain per admitted proof into
  `data/artefacts/<id>/`: the deriver (claude) writes `derivation.tex`, the
  computer generates and executes `check.py` into `check-results.md`, and
  the critic (codex) writes `critique.md` with a clean / revise / reject
  verdict. A revise verdict makes the next `analyse` run re-derive with the
  critique as input.
- **Context.** Per-technique primers in `context/` ground the deriver:
  elementary, analytic, topological, algebraic.

## Usage

```bash
uv run infprime scan       # collect seed corpus + arXiv watch hits
uv run infprime triage     # admit + label pending candidates
uv run infprime analyse    # derive, check, critique admitted proofs
uv run infprime run        # scan, then triage, then analyse, then digest
```

`--agent claude|codex` selects the CLI for the scan/triage/derive/check
stages; `--critic-agent` selects the critic's CLI (codex by default, for
cross-model review).

## Tests

```bash
uv run pytest
```


